data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda

Your expression tree construction **won't compile**. Replace it entirely:

```csharp
// EF Core 10 — simple lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery is no longer needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will auto-append a number (e.g., `Street1`). This generates a column-rename migration.

**b) Nested complex types use full path.** Your `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was previously `BillingAddress_City` — it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin existing names with `HasColumnName()`:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

Then run `dotnet ef migrations add VerifyNoChanges` — it should be empty if names are correct.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter. Your implementation won't compile until you add it:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new: redacted SQL safe for logging
    { /* logging — use logCommandText instead of command.CommandText */ }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) — they all received the same new parameter.
